e is also found in Romania, Slovakia, Croatia, and Serbia, and also among Rusyns (in Serbia and Croatia). See also   Pop   2 and   Popa  .","English: variant of   Pape   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Papp","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Laszlo, Zoltan, Geza, Istvan, Gabor, Miklos, Tibor, Arpad, Denes, Imre, Attila.","German (Bavaria, Tyrol): from Middle High German <i>pap</i> ‘baby food’, Dutch <i>pap</i> ‘porridge, pap’, hence perhaps a nickname denoting someone who had lost his teeth or subsisted on a meager diet.","Hungarian: from <i>pap</i> ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’, probably an occupational name for someone in the service of a priest or a nickname for a pious person. This surname is also found in Romania and Slovakia, and also among Rusyns. Compare   Pap   and   Pop  ."]}]},{"name":"Griffith","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh (Carmarthenshire and western England): from the Old Welsh personal name <i>Gruffudd</i>, Old Welsh <i>Grip(p)iud</i>, composed of the elements <i>grip</i>, of uncertain significance, + <i>iud</i> ‘chief, lord’."],"variants":[{"name":"Griffieth","meanings":["Variant of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griff","meanings":["English: topographic name for someone living near a pit or hollow, from Middle English <i>grif</i> ‘pit, hollow, narrow valley’ (Old Norse <i>gryfja</i>), or a habitational name from Griff in Warwickshire, Griffe in Derbyshire, or Griff Farm in Rievaulx, North Yorkshire, all probably named with this word.","Welsh and English: from the Welsh personal name <i>Gryff</i>, a short form of <i>Gruffudd</i>. See   Griffith  .","German: variant of   Greif   1."]},{"name":"Kerfoot","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Cheshire):","habitational name, probably from Carefoot, near Myerscough (Lancashire).","possibly a variant of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griffes","meanings":["Welsh: altered form of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griffeth","meanings":["Altered form of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griffiths","meanings":["Welsh (Glamorgan and western England): Anglicized form of the patronymic <i>(ap) Gruffudd</i>, from Old Welsh <i>Grippiud</i> (see   Griffith  )."]},{"name":"Griffth","meanings":["Variant of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griffitt","meanings":["Altered form of   Griffith  ."]}]},{"name":"Jenkin","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, which is derived from the medieval given name <i>Jankin</i>. This was a pet form of the boy's name   Jan  , with the diminutive suffix <i>-kin</i>. The modern given name is popular in Wales, where the surnames <i>Jenkin</i> and <i>Jenkins</i> are common."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Jenkin ap Griffith was born about 1368, in Glamorgan, Wales. She had at least 1 son with Jenkin ap Griffith."},"et":{"about 1368–":"umbes 1368–Surnud","1364–Male":"1364–Surnud","1390–Male":"1390–Surnud","1368–Female":"1368–Surnud","abt. 1390":"umbes 1390","1368":"1368","1364":"1364","about 1368":"umbes 1368","1390":"1390","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","of Glyn-Nedd, Glmrgn., Wls.":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1368–":"noin 1368–Kuollut","1364–Male":"1364–Kuollut","1390–Male":"1390–Kuollut","1368–Female":"1368–Kuollut","abt. 1390":"noin 1390","1368":"1368","1364":"1364","about 1368":"noin 1368","1390":"1390","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","of Glyn-Nedd, Glmrgn., Wls.":"Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1368–":"environ 1368–Décédée","1364–Male":"1364–Décédé","1390–Male":"1390–Décédé","1368–Female":"1368–Décédée","abt. 1390":"environ 1390","1368":"1368","1364":"1364","about 1368":"environ 1368","1390":"1390","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Galles","of Glyn-Nedd, Glmrgn., Wls.":"Glamorgan, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Jenkin ap Griffith est née environ 1368, à Glamorgan, Galles. Elle 